            <li>Serves 2: 1</li></ul>
        <h2 id="pasta">Pasta with Garlic and Olive Oil #2</h2>
        <ul>
            
        <li>Time 3: 12-15 min</li>
            <li>Serves 3: 2</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td id="recipe1">1 ripe avocado,2 slices of bread,Salt and pepper</td>   
                 <td>2</td>
                   </tr> 
                   <tr>
            <td id="recipe2"> large eggs
1 tablespoon butter,salt,black pepper</td>   
                 <td>2</td>
                 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr>
            <td id="recipe3">spaghetti or other pasta,garlic cloves,olive oil,salt, black pepper</td>   
                 <td>2</td>
                 
                   </tr> 
            </tbody>
        </table>
        <p id="steps1">1st Recipe</p>
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Toast the bread in a toaster or oven for 3-4 minutes, until golden brown.
</p>

             <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Cut the avocado in half, remove the pit, and scoop the flesh into a small bowl.
</p> 
<p><strong>Step 3:</strong>Spread the mashed avocado evenly over the toasted bread slices.
</p>
<p><strong>Step 4:</strong>Serve immediately and enjoy.</p>

<p id="steps2">2nd Recipe</p>

<p><strong>Step 1:</strong>Crack the eggs into a bowl, add the salt and pepper, and whisk them together until smooth. 
</p>

             <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> 
             Heat 1 tablespoon of butter in a non-stick pan over medium heat and Pour the eggs into the pan and let them sit undisturbed for a few seconds.

</p> 
<p><strong>Step 3:</strong>Add the thinly sliced garlic to the oil and sauté for 2-3 minutes until the garlic turns golden brown

</p>

<p><strong>Step 4:</strong> Continue stirring for another 1-2 minutes, until the eggs are fully cooked but still soft. 
 </p>
 
 <p><strong>Step 5:</strong>Remove from heat and serve immediately.
 
 <p id="steps3">3rd Recipe</p>
 <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Crack the eggs into a bowl, add the salt and pepper, and whisk them together until smooth
</p>

             <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Add the thinly sliced garlic to the oil and sauté for 2-3 minutes until the garlic turns golden brown
</p> 
<p><strong>Step 3:</strong>Once the pasta is cooked, drain it and immediately toss it in the pan with the garlic and olive oil.</p>

<p><strong>Step 4:</strong> Season with salt, pepper, and optional red pepper flakes.
 </p>
 


